</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="357" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="11.[144,1352,2062,2726]" pageId="11" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[145,411,2416,2449]" pageId="11" pageNumber="357">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but as with other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gervais" authorityYear="1850" box="[440,590,2456,2489]" class="Mammalia" family="Hyperoodontidae" genus="Mesoplodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cetacea" pageId="11" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Mesoplodon</taxonomicName>
, the Spade-toothed Whale likely eats deep-water squid and deep-water fish. Like other species of beaked whales,it likely forages at depths greater than 500 m for much ofits life.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
